{{Quote|To understand us, there is one place to start. Let me introduce you to the Embrace of Pain.|Shedao Shai|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide II: Ruin">''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide II: Ruin]]''</ref>}}
The '''Embrace of Pain''' was an [[Bioengineering/Legends|organic]], rack-like restraint used to [[Torture/Legends|torture]] [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]]. A victim was kept upside down in restraint bands, and tortured while the creature would read the electrochemical outputs of the victim's nerve impulses and evaluate their [[Brain/Legends|brain]] chemistry. The resultant data was used to keep the pain at constant and optimum levels. The device had a number of different methods for inducing pain, including stretching of ligaments and joints, acid, electric shocks, sharp devices, needles, thorns, and injected biotoxins. In at least one case, the victim was stripped naked, and all of his hairs pulled out. When the victim was at the brink of dying, the Embrace would tend to the prisoner's body by lowering them to the floor and letting them [[Sleep/Legends|sleep]] for a time, while tending wounds and injecting the prisoner with enough water and nutrients to keep them alive. The [[Yuuzhan Vong]] did not consider it torture, and some Yuuzhan Vong, such as the members of [[Domain Shai]], used the Embrace of Pain as a form of [[Meditation/Legends|meditation]].

The device could induce so much pain that it was capable of turning even the most noble [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]].

==History==
{{Quote|The Vong call it the Embrace of Pain. The more you struggle to escape, the more pain it inflicts.|Darth Krayt, to Cade Skywalker|<ref name="Legacy (2006) 18">[[Legacy (2006) 18|''Legacy'' (2006) 18]]</ref>}}
[[File:HettHangsOutWithVergere-L18.jpg|thumb|left|170px|[[Darth Krayt|A'Sharad Hett]] undergoes the Embrace of Pain.]]
When [[Elegos A'Kla]] turned himself over to the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] to learn more about them, [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Shedao Shai]] introduced him to the Embrace of Pain as a way to learn about the Yuuzhan Vong, scandalizing his subordinates. [[Darth Krayt|A'Sharad Hett]] was placed in the Embrace of Pain following his capture by the Yuuzhan Vong, as was [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] after being [[Mission to Myrkr|captured]] at [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]].

In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], Jacen would use the last known Embrace of Pain to try converting his cousin [[Ben Skywalker]] to the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]], just as he himself had begun to turn. The experience of being tortured by the device was so traumatizing that even years later, hearing the word "embrace" would illicit an instant and visceral response from the young Skywalker.

Darth Krayt would later do the same with [[Cade Skywalker]], having previously encountered the Embrace after completing his apprenticeship with [[XoXaan]] on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] and being captured by the Yuuzhan Vong. As [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]], Krayt would use the Embrace as part of the training for certain members of the [[One Sith]], including [[Darth Nihl]], in order to push them towards the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. He would also have the Embrace of Pain installed in the [[Embrace of Pain chamber|underlevels]] of the [[Temple of the Sith]].

During her plot to use Cade as a test subject for a new weapon to be used by Darth Krayt's successor as Dark Lord of the Sith, [[Darth Maladi]] tortured [[Deliah Blue]] in an Embrace of Pain that resisted the use of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] against it and caused even more pain to the prisoner.

